race.description: Wallace Construction In Memory Of Boof Marshall Hcp
race.comment: MASTER GEE (2) doesn't win out of turn, scoring just two times from 32 starts. Again, tasted defeat last start when seventh over 1100m at this track, beaten 2.5 lengths. Perfectly placed in this easier grade and is sure to give this a mighty shake. RICHUNCLEMONEYBAGS (4) finished sixth two runs back then did well last start but found one better over 1200m at Gayndah, beaten only half a length. Taking on a better line-up this time but he is up to the challenge. ADVISER (7) doesn't win out of turn but left a good impression last time out when beaten half a length into second over 1100m at Inverell. Expected to cross from wide out. One of the main contenders. INDIAN THUNDER (11) has been out of the winner's list for a long time, last start finished eighth at this track over 1300m. Perfectly placed and is sure to play a pivotal role.
